==English==
===Etymology===
Representing Greek [[μητροπόλεις]].

===Noun===
'''metropoleis'''

# = [[metropolises]] ''(usually with reference to ancient Greece)''
#:*'''1998''': The larger '''''metropoleis''''' were sizeable communities: Hermopolis had eprhaps as many as 40,000 inhabitants, Oxyrhynchos maybe around 25,000. — Jane Rowlandson, ''Women and Society in Greek and Roman Egypt'' (Cambridge 2003, p. 12)
#:*'''1996''': The role which the '''metropoleis''' developed as administrative centres for their nomes had always been inherent in the Ptolomeic system but the evidence suggests that it was much enhanced under the Romans. — Alan K. Bowman, ''The Cambridge Ancient History'', ed. Bowman, Champlin, Lintott (Cambridge 2004, p. 684)
#:*'''1991''': We have already mentioned that some colonies eventually became '''''metropoleis'''''. — I M Drakonoff, ''Early Antiquity'' (Chicago 1991, p. 363)